address: Xã Phú Xuân, Huyện Bình Xuyên, Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc
thought:
**Navigating the Administrative Unit Change**

Okay, so I'm looking at how to pinpoint the new administrative unit for "Xã Phú Xuân, Huyện Bình Xuyên, Tỉnh Vĩnh Phúc."  The initial task is to figure out if Vĩnh Phúc still exists.  Checking for province resolutions related to 60-NQ/TW, I see that Vĩnh Phúc was merged with Phú Thọ and Hòa Bình, becoming "Tỉnh Phú Thọ."  Good, that clears up the province.

Next, I need to see if there are any changes to "Xã Phú Xuân." I'm diving into "Other resolutions" focusing on "Phú Xuân" within the context of either Vĩnh Phúc or the new province, Phú Thọ.  After a quick scan through resolutions like 1654/NQ-UBTVQH15, 1660/NQ-UBTVQH15, and so on, I realize those are irrelevant because they pertain to places with the name "Phú Xuân" in other provinces.

Finally, I reach **1676/NQ-UBTVQH15 (Phú Thọ)** - Bingo!  This resolution is key because Phú Thọ is the new province.  In item 87, it states something crucial: "Sắp xếp toàn bộ diện tích tự nhiên, quy mô dân số của thị trấn Thanh Lãng, thị trấn Đạo Đức, xã Tân Phong và xã Phú Xuân thành xã mới có tên gọi là **xã Xuân Lãng**."  This clearly states "Xã Phú Xuân" is merged into the newly named "Xã Xuân Lãng."  While resolution 88 mentions a new "xã Bình Xuyên", it is not directly relevant to "Xã Phú Xuân" according to resolution 87.

Therefore, my conclusion is that the old "Xã Phú Xuân" is now part of the new "Xã Xuân Lãng" in the province of Phú Thọ.
